    {
      "id": "1012761",
      "title": "",
      "description": "Framingham/Worcester Line Commuter Rail service will operate between Grafton and South Station. Riders can take shuttle buses between Worcester and Grafton.\r\n\r\nTravel Time:\r\nRiders using the shuttle buses should budget extra travel time. For example, a rider traveling to South Station from Worcester should budget at least 25 extra minutes of travel in addition to their regular trip time.\r\n\r\nAccessibility Information:\r\nThere will be no accessible vans provided, as all shuttle buses are equipped with a wheelchair lift and all shuttle stops are accessible.\r\n\r\nShuttle Stops:\r\n\r\nWorcester Union Station:\r\nWorcester Union Station Bus Terminal (Bays #1-3)\r\n\r\nGrafton:\r\nGrafton Station Parking Lot\r\n\r\nAffected stations:\r\nGrafton\r\nWorcester",
      "severity": 8,
      "route_id": "unknown"
